13.3 Fetching Data (SwiftUI Example)
Here is a factual comparison of exactly how you retrieve data from a robust database in both ecosystems.






NoteWhat does a SQL query structurally look like in Node/Javascript?





// Raw un-typed database execution
const users = await db.query("SELECT * FROM User ORDER BY name ASC");



Swift Equivalent (SwiftUI): In Swift, because there is an unbreakable, compiler-checked link between the visual .xcdatamodeld file and the executing View, we extract information directly inside the physical view using a Property Wrapper called @FetchRequest (or @Query in SwiftData).
import SwiftUI

struct UserListView: View {
    // ⬇️ This is the executing Query. 
    // It strictly commands the database: "Give me all Users, structurally sorted by their name."
    @FetchRequest(sortDescriptors: [SortDescriptor(\.name)]) 
    var users: FetchedResults&lt;User&gt; 

    var body: some View {
        List(users) { user in
            // ⬇️ We mechanically use the exact physical 'name' property we built in the visual map
            Text(user.name ?? "Unknown User") 
        }
    }
}
